1. create a file "test"


2. open cmd from there


3. check version : python --version


4. TO INSTALL VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENT, WE REQUIRE VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENT PACKAGE --
   py -m pip install --user virtualenv

   
5. NEXT, WE NEED TO CREATE A ENVIRONMENT --
   py -m venv exp12

   
6. NEXT WE HAVE TO ACTIVATE --
   code .  = to check if we got all scripts & others.

   
7. go back to cmd and type --
   .\exp12\scripts\activate

   
8. NEXT, we have to INSTALL DJANGO FRAME WORK-
   TO CHECK IF DJANGO IS PRESENT OR NOT --
   django-admin --version

   
9. If it is not there....we need to install it --
   pip install django 

   
10. To check whether all packages are installed in this package type -
    pip list

    
11. NEXT IS DJANGO PROJECT CREATION
syntax : django-admin startproject exp13


12. in cmd type : cd exp13


13. type : code .


14. NEXT THING IS TO RUN DJANGO PROJECT


15. manage.py : it acts as the cli to execute any project or run django project


16. go to cmd : py manage.py runserver


17. init.py = tells the starting of the application


18. settings.py = here we configure all the settings
